<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1191123-does-this-remind-anyone-of-disney-s-the">Does this remind anyone of Disney&#39;s The Black Cauldron (based off the books series by Lloyd Alexander)?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1191123'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F18392.The_Lost_Years_of_Merlin">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1191123-does-this-remind-anyone-of-disney-s-the">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1191123-does-this-remind-anyone-of-disney-s-the">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/8130785-kara"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1336797351i/8130785._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/8130785-kara">Kara</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Lloyd Alexander specifically references the Welsh myth/epic The Mabinogian (good book, in a classicy sort of way) as an inspiration, which includes a <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Lloyd Alexander specifically references the Welsh myth/epic The Mabinogian (good book, in a classicy sort of way) as an inspiration, which includes a number of elements found in both of these books. Barron talks in his prologue about the extensive research he did regarding Merlin and how his childhood is absent from any of the many Arthurian sources. It makes sense he would dip into other mythos from the same region. Rhiannon was my first tip off that he might be using it as a source.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link1088677" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=1088677&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F1191123-does-this-remind-anyone-of-disney-s-the%2Fanswers%2F1088677-lloyd-alexander">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
</ul>

</div>
</div>

</div>

</div>
