<div id="review_2805170395" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2805170395" />
    <a title="Alexis" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/89622319-alexis"><img alt="Alexis" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1556658539p2/89622319.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2805170395?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alexis" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alexis" href="/user/show/89622319-alexis">Alexis</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780142418895" href="/book/show/9783478-the-lost-years">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/89622319-alexis?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2805170395" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11967162899112036133">This was an interesting take on the Merlin mythos and a great starting point for young readers to get into Arthurian literature. If you have a young reader you want to get interested in this stuff, reach for this one, absolutely.<br/><br/>Unfortunately, I came into this as an adult, already fascinated with Arthurian legend (so some of this felt a little far fetched) and right on the heels of Mary Stewart&apos;s excellent Merlin saga, so I think this fell a little flatter than it would have otherwise.</span>
  <span id="freeText11967162899112036133" style="display:none">This was an interesting take on the Merlin mythos and a great starting point for young readers to get into Arthurian literature. If you have a young reader you want to get interested in this stuff, reach for this one, absolutely.<br /><br />Unfortunately, I came into this as an adult, already fascinated with Arthurian legend (so some of this felt a little far fetched) and right on the heels of Mary Stewart's excellent Merlin saga, so I think this fell a little flatter than it would have otherwise.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11967162899112036133" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


