        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1595578668" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16337836625277280831">A book for all ages. <br/><br/>In this excellent tale of the wizard between the mortal and divine, voices appear in Merlin&apos;s head and he wants his memory back to know who and what he is. Later Merlin learns, like Luke Sky Walker in Star Wars, that his father is the evil one. It is in Chapter 4 &quot;Sacred Time&quot; that Merlin recreates the classic myth of the eternal return, rebirth. <br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText16337836625277280831" style="display:none">A book for all ages. <br /><br />In this excellent tale of the wizard between the mortal and divine, voices appear in Merlin's head and he wants his memory back to know who and what he is. Later Merlin learns, like Luke Sky Walker in Star Wars, that his father is the evil one. It is in Chapter 4 "Sacred Time" that Merlin recreates the classic myth of the eternal return, rebirth. <br /><br /></span>
