        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2673567153" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6005927540924015797">This book is incredibly fun and interesting for young adults as it takes Emrys all the way to his homeland and he meets hist father and chooses the name Merlin. I am not giving anything away by saying this. The characters are great and provide a sense of belonging and loss at the appropriate times.<br/><br/>I will say that parts of this book remind me of the vague memories I have of a book by Lloyd Alexander called &quot;The Black Cauldron&quot; especially the ending. I really enjoyed that book as well and I think </span>
  <span id="freeText6005927540924015797" style="display:none">This book is incredibly fun and interesting for young adults as it takes Emrys all the way to his homeland and he meets hist father and chooses the name Merlin. I am not giving anything away by saying this. The characters are great and provide a sense of belonging and loss at the appropriate times.<br /><br />I will say that parts of this book remind me of the vague memories I have of a book by Lloyd Alexander called "The Black Cauldron" especially the ending. I really enjoyed that book as well and I think this one is very similar because the authors knew each other.</span>
